#' @details The Matrix-T distribution \eqn{\boldsymbol{X} \sim \textrm{Matrix-T}(\boldsymbol{\Lambda}, \boldsymbol{\Sigma}, \boldsymbol{\Psi}, \nu)}{X ~ Matrix-T(\Lambda, \Sigma, \Psi, \nu)} on a random matrix \eqn{\boldsymbol{X}_{p \times q}}{X_(p x q)} is the marginal distribution of \eqn{\boldsymbol{X}}{X} in \eqn{(\boldsymbol{X}, \boldsymbol{V}) \sim \textrm{MNIW}(\boldsymbol{\Lambda}, \boldsymbol{\Sigma}, \boldsymbol{\Psi}, \nu)}{(X, V) ~ MNIW(\Lambda, \Sigma, \Psi, \nu)}, where the Matrix-Normal Inverse-Wishart (MNIW) distribution is defined in \code{\link{MNIW}}.
